Conditions.Mandatory: Fireplaces shall be included in the gross floor area

Exceptions.Explicit deviations: Fireplaces not connected to the house are treated like accessory structures
Exceptions.Special cases: Count towards FAR if greater than 120 s.f.; Count towards lot coverage always

Conditions.Mandatory: Sheds, planters, and other projections that are higher than 5' count toward gross floor area

Constants.Procedures: Count once towards the gross floor area

Conditions.Mandatory: All configurations of chimneys count once towards the gross floor area

Exceptions.Explicit deviations: Chimneys on the upper floors do not count

extracted_rules.rule: Miscellaneous Appendages and Gross Floor Area

Qualifiers.Exclusions: May not be located in the required yards

Conditions.Mandatory: Miscellaneous appendages greater than 5' in height do count toward gross floor area

Exceptions.Explicit deviations: Neither appendages nor noise-producing equipment may be located in the required yards

Conditions.Mandatory: Prohibition of the construction of new wood-burning fireplaces

Relationships.Cross-references: See Chapter 9.06.030 for details and exceptions
